The paper deals with constructing linear codes and determining their weight enumerators, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and coding theory (cs.CR). The codes are also suitable for secret sharing schemes, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The use of defining sets and weight enumerators also suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to computer communications (cs.CC) and signal processing (cs.SI) due to the potential applications of the constructed codes.
